Conditional Statements:are used to make the set of instrctions(block of code)(conditional block) execute only when the given condition is true
>>They are used to decide whether the code has to be executed or skip based on the given condition
>>execute in a sequence line by line


Block of Code:Set of instructions
>It will execute only when that specific condition is true


Condition:An expression that evaluates an result(True or False) 
Eg:console.log(5>6)

Methods:

1)if: only one possible condition;if the condition is true it will execute otherwise it will skip

Syntax:
       if(condition){
      block of code
}

Ex:
    let a=4
    let b=5
    if(a<b){
        document.write("hello venky","<br>")
    }
    document.write("brilliant puli")

Output:hello venky
brilliant puli



2)if-else

Example:
        let a=4
    let b=5
    if(a>b){
     document.write("hello venky","<br>")
    }else{
        document.write("hi Reddy","<br>")
    }
    document.write("brilliant puli","<br>")

Output:hi Reddy
brilliant puli


3)else if:
     Example:let age =prompt("Enter Your Age?")
let name=prompt("Enter your name?")
if(age<18){
    alert(name+"You are too young to marry")
}else if(age>35){
    alert(name+"You are too old to marry")
}else{
    alert(name+"Perfect age to marry")
}
alert("Welcome to My world")

Output:Venky ReddyPerfect age to marry



